  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guarantee specialized child protection services and access to education for children displaced and returned in South and East Ninewa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The present proposal aims to guarantee the protection, resilience and access to education to IDPs and returnees children in the area of Al-Hmandanya and Haja Ali/Qayara. Two schools will be rehabilitated and PSS activities will be delivered there in coordination with the formal school. This will be the entry point also to reach out of school children and start a process of school enrollment passing through non formal education where needed. A special attention and specialized support will be given to vulnerable children: two child protection units will be set up to provide case management and referral. One team will be fully dedicated to identification and follow up of unaccompanied and separated minors, with the possibility to reach also other locations if needed. Another team will work exclusively with children with disabilities providing them also physiotherapy and psychological support and working for a possessively social inclusion.  Another special focus is given to adolescents and youths, youths network will be set up in order to provide learning and recreational activities, life skill trainings and vocational trainings. Finally, community will be directly involved in the process of establishing child protection local committees to start a mechanism of community based child protection. At the same time, also teachers will be trained to skill up their capacity in terms of child protection, inclusive education, PSS and classroom management.</narrative>
  </description>
